Dream Out Loud Center, Inc.
July 23 at 8:49 PM ·

The deadline for applications has been extended to Sunday, July 26th, as we still have some openings available!

We are currently recruiting for our FREE Summer Creative Careers Program "Arts in August!" for youth ages 13 - 18 who are interested in songwriting, digital music production, illustration and graphic design.

Classes start on August 4, 2020 and will be held on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 3:00pm - 5:00pm through August 27th.

Space is extremely limited. Adherance to all COVID 19 regulations and social distancing guidelines will be mandatory to be eligible for enrollment.

You can mail completed applications to Dream Out Loud, 1 Johnny Cake Hill, New Bedford MA 02740, fax to (508) 990-9088, or email to information@dreamoutloudnow.org.

Please share with any youth who may be interested!

shared_text:
Little People's College, Inc/L.P. College, Inc
May 6 at 8:10 AM ·

CHARADES
A classic game of charades is not only a silly way for kids to be expressive, but it’s also a quiet activity for indoor play that can go on for as little or as much time as you want. Charades gets kids up and moving while helping them become better communicators in a way that’s fun and interactive.
Kids can even make up their own categories for the game in addition to the classics: TV shows, songs, sports, animals, professions, etc. All you need is a bit of imagination and a good hat or bowl for shuffling up your ideas to get started. Here are a few lists to get you started!

shared_text:
New Bedford Whaling Museum
April 29 at 11:15 AM ·

LIGHTING the WAY: Join the Whaling Museum's public art initiative #LightingTheWayForAll! We're marking the 100th anniversary of the 19th Amendment recognizing some women’s right to vote, honoring the unfinished legacy of the women’s suffrage movement, and celebrating historic women who forged the path and lit the way for us all: YOU can help!

Local students have narrated video profiles of 10 civically engaged women from the Lighting the Way project. You can help decide which of these remarkable women will be the subjects of public art to be unveiled at the end of the summer. Through the entire month of May, you can view the videos and VOTE for your favorites.

For more information visit http://ow.ly/MQpZ50zrbhy. #LightingTheWayForAll

South Coast LGBTQ Network
April 15 at 9:02 AM ·

We are excited to share that NB-AGLY A Perfect Place have additional funding that allows them to give youth/young adults an incentive to join their weekly virtual group Thursdays from 5pm-7pm on NB-AGLY A Perfect Place private group Facebook page for LGBTQ+ youth/young adults ages 14-24.

Starting April 16th when youth/young adults attend 3 virtual groups they will receive a $50 gift card from NB-AGLY A Perfect Place.

To be eligible for the $50 gift card they must sign in to the NB-AGLY Facebook virtual group by 5:15pm and stay until the group ends. At the end of each group their name will be added to the list of who attended. Those who attend 3 virtual groups will receive a $50 gift card.

NB-AGLY A Perfect Place support LGBTQ+ youth/young adults ages 14-24 in the South Coast.
Share this with your LGBTQ+ friends ages 14-24.
Have them join the NB-AGLY A Perfect Place Facebook page.

New Bedford Counts 2020 Census
February 18 at 7:16 AM ·

Answering the census is COMPLETELY CONFIDENTIAL. In 1982, the U.S. Supreme Court confirmed that even addresses are confidential and cannot be disclosed through legal discovery or the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA). In 2010, the U.S. Justice Department determined that the Patriot Act does not override the law that protects the confidentiality of individual census responses. No court of law can subpoena census responses. So reply without worry _ and with the assurance that you responses help your family, your community and your country. #Census2020 #EveryonecountsinNewBedford

on March 12! Submit your original art inspired by the Whaling Museum's history project "Lighting the Way: Historic Women of the SouthCoast." SUBMISSION DEADLINE is February 23. Join us for the Whaling Museum’s ART WEEK - offered just in time for February school vacation, Feb. 17-21! Students in middle and high school: you can explore the Museum’s extensive collection of art and create your own works of art in a series of hands-on workshops. All ages can explore hands-on Art Stations in the Museum’s Jacobs Family Gallery.

Workshops are FREE, but REGISTRATION is REQUIRED. Art Stations are completely free for everyone! Various other activities are free for Whaling Museum members and with regular paid admission to the Museum. Register and view the full schedule of activities at https://www.whalingmuseum.org/programs/art-week-2020/.

ART WEEK programs are supported in part by a grant from the New Bedford Local Cultural Council , a local agency which is supported by Mass Cultural Council ,a state agency.

shared_text:
Dream Out Loud Center, Inc.
September 29, 2019 at 7:06 PM ·

We are still recruiting for our FREE Fall Creative Careers Program for middle and high school youth who are interested in songwriting, recording, music production, performance, illustration, graphic design and film making.

We invite you to visit Dream Out Loud Center, 1 Johnny Cake Hill in downtown New Bedford, during our informational sign up sessions this week on:

Tuesday, 10/1, 2pm - 5pm
Wednesday, 10/2, 2pm - 5pm
Thursday, 10/3, 2pm - 5pm

New Bedford Public Schools
September 25, 2019 at 9:22 AM ·

STATEMENT ON NON-CREDIBLE THREATS

New Bedford Public Schools is aware of threats made to schools and is working closely with the New Bedford Police Department, which have determined them to be not credible. Police report that New Bedford is not the only city to receive such threats.

Superintendent Thomas Anderson said, “We are working aggressively with NBPD regarding a non-credible threat made against public schools in general. At this time we are remaining in session, and as a precaution we will be on high alert. As normal, we are supporting our schools through this process.”

shared_text:
New Bedford Parks, Recreation & Beaches
May 15, 2019 at 2:10 PM ·

It is not too late to register for the NE Patriots Alumni Free Football Clinic! ‘Football For YOU’ was created by Patriots Alumni in partnership with the New England Patriots Foundation and the NFL Foundation to bring the fundamentals of football to children in and around New England. This unique half-day, non-contact free clinic stresses leadership, teamwork, and commitment to over 200 young athletes (ages 9-14). Each participant will rotate through (6) 15 minute stations which all represent a position on the field. No equipment is needed. Each clinic is coached by Patriot Alumni in conjunction with New Bedford high school staff and players. Returning this year for parents and guardians are (3) optional 15 minute information sessions that will address ‘The way you win matters’, sportsmanship, and nutrition education. We are grateful to share our meal sponsor for all camps, for the second year in a row, is Domino’s pizza.

WOW! Just announced: New Bedford High School is one of the top 50 schools competing in the 10th annual #VansCustomCulture competition! Custom Culture is a national high school customization competition using blank Vans shoes to be customized around specific themes. Vans is working to bring attention to diminishing arts education nationwide and the importance of youth creativity and self-expression by donating $75,000 towards the winning school’s art program, and $10,000 to the four runner-up's. NBHS is now one step closer! Voting opens today through May 3. VOTE FOR NBHS here: customculture.vans.com You can vote once a day, every day. GO Whalers!

Community Boating Center
April 11, 2019 at 1:06 PM ·

We collected a five gallon bucket’s worth of trash in just a few minutes today along the street and beach in front of our building. Most of this would have ended up in the ocean! Do what you can to reduce/reuse/recycle and prevent marine debris!

Come and see what we’ve done with some other marine debris tonight at AHA! New Bedford’s Earth Day Eve Procession at 5pm. We’ll also be showing off the marine trash skimmer going into NB harbor in conjunction with Port of New Bedford and Clean Ocean Access. #beoceanfriendly

Round the Bend Farm
April 4, 2019 at 1:25 PM ·

Round the Bend Farm is seeking New Bedford area youth applicants (17-21) for our 2019 Youth Environmental Justice Team. Youth should have an interest in African & Indigenous History, Environmental Justice, Environmental Sustainability, Food Preparation, Cooking, Leadership Development, Team Building: and be comfortable doing physical farm labor outdoors in all weather conditions this Summer.
Applications Accepted Until Friday April 5th at 4pm and are available at www.BIT.LY/RTBJOB
These positions are funded through YouthWorks Summer Jobs Program managed by MassHire Greater New Bedford Career Center
For more info contact at Erik Andrade at 508-938-5127 or Erik@RoundTheBendFarm.org

post_text:
Our Resource Fair is only a month away! We're sorry to say that we had a mistake on our flyer and have included an updated one here. If you shared our first version, please share this updated one and we're sorry for any confusion.
The good news is that we already have 19 organizations who will be represented there that day so it's a great opportunity to find out what they have to offer! Participating organizations include NorthStar Learning Centers, Inc., Community Boating Center, Southeastern Regional Transit Authority (SRTA), Superflat NB, YWCA Girls Exclusive and Dennison Memorial Community Center. Stay tuned for other participating organizations!
